# Database Rules

## ORM
- Drizzle ORM only
- Schema in `packages/db/src/schema/`
- One file per table group

## Naming
- Tables: snake_case, plural (users, agent_tasks)
- Columns: snake_case
- IDs: `id` (UUID v7)
- Timestamps: `created_at`, `updated_at`
- Foreign keys: `<table>_id`
- Booleans: `is_*`, `has_*`, `requires_*`

## ID Strategy
- UUID v7 (sortable, time-ordered)
- Generated app-side
- Never expose internal sequences

## Indexes
- All foreign keys indexed
- Lookup columns indexed
- Composite indexes for common query patterns
- Partial indexes where applicable
- HNSW for pgvector

## Constraints
- NOT NULL by default
- Foreign keys with ON DELETE behavior explicit
- CHECK constraints for enums
- UNIQUE for natural keys

## Migrations
- One migration per change
- Up + down required
- Idempotent where possible
- Test on production-sized data
- Backfill scripts separate

## Queries
- Always tenant-scoped
- Use transactions for multi-step writes
- Limit + offset OR cursor pagination
- No SELECT *
- Explicit columns

## JSONB
- Use sparingly
- Index with GIN if queried
- Schema-validate before insert (Zod)

## Soft Delete
- `deleted_at` column nullable
- Filter in default query
- Hard delete for compliance (GDPR)

## Audit Trail
- audit_logs table for security events
- Triggers for sensitive tables (V2)